The evidence with the title 'State Of Florida ' says Florida is the southernmost contiguous state in the United States. The state is bordered to the west by the Gulf Of Mexico , to the northwest by Alabama, to the north by Georgia , to the east by the Atlantic Ocean, and to the south by the Straits Of Florida . Florida is the 22nd-most extensive (65,755 sq mi or 170,300 km2), the  ... Florida 's $1.0 trillion economy is the fourth largest in the United States. 
